From Pasi Fr nti Subject Re Helsinki Stockholm NHL expansion MLINDROOS Marcus Lindroos INF writes Not too low perhaps but surely not as high as that of an European NHL The Finnish team for example would contain all players currently on the national team plus a top class foreigner or They would be in an entirely different league than TPS or Jokerit both of whom have perhaps a dozen players of international class if even Why settle for a minor league when you could have the best It is no matter what you call the teams Jokerit and TPS or Helsinki Tornado and Turku Typhoon the best palyers in Finland would eventually end up in those teams anyway if they were in the big I'd rather spend Marks to watch the Helsinki Tornado play Montreal the NY Rangers or Los Angeles than Marks for the privilege to see Jokerit JypHT or even Djurgardens There's nothing like the NHL Unrealistic for Maybe we should first just expand Finnish league to allow teams from Baltic countries to entry Then others will get interested in the idea that maybe one should settle something The ultimate goal as you want it would be European Division in does that make a final with an Europan team against Norht American